arch:property.oc:show_val: X1 is a bone ring fragment. Medium, fragmented unit with the identifiables mainly from sheep/goat. Some of the bone has been charred and little has suffered from digestion. X6 is an equid scapula. A couple of fish jaws were recovered from the 4mm flotation sample, which was recorded for diagnostics only. NR 2003: More material was found later. This looks like fill. There is a mix of animal sizes, fragment sizes, and surface conditions. Most is rather fragmented and worn, but there are some large pieces and delicate items, such as perinatal sheep/goat. There is a pathological cattle ankle, and a pile of cattle horn core crumbles that was probably once a fair-size chunk, but not a huge piece. Last number = 240
